			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I believe it has to do with the buffing bug that's reared it's ugly head since the "buff icon" patch during mid prime time last week to fix the flaming pink buff icons.
<br />

<br />
On raids  numerous people have noted a buff message landed on them, such as the emote, "XXX looks like the dead", when DMF was cast on 2 of our pullers in water on a recent Ofossaa raid. Point is, they actually see the spell emoted that it landed but it never gave a buff icon. So, newly rezzed puller  thinks he is EB'd, goes of throughout the plane of Water to finish clearing Ofossaa room and ends up downing far away from camp.
<br />
MT, add tanks, clerics ect have all noticed this bug on recent raids, and it's highly unrepeatable. It just affects the buffer all of a sudden, and their buffs will no longer land on anyone. Camping and returning usually seems to fix this however. But the same can be noticed for the buffee.
<br />
Yesterday during the Fennin script our MT fell during the first 1/5 of the fight. After being dragged and rezzed and rebuffed, quite a few buffs would not land on the fallen MT.  Virtue, focus, SoP, Speed, etc, as you can see, this is a tremendous bug, and it is affecting our gameplay and raiding abilities. Granted we still won, but playing around bugs like this is becoming quite annoying and cumbersome.
<br />

<br />
I assume the same is happening for pets that's being reported here. Sometimes, just like buffs, won't take on characters, even though they give the proper emotes of them landing. I've seen the spell emote of bo5 landing on my pet recently, but a /pet report health shows my pet has 0 buffs. I have not noticed this with pet weapons , beause lately I dont even bother equipping pets. In a raid setting, I just have him out and on /hold for siphon and to send in on boss fights.
<br />

<br />
And not related to magicians or pets, but those god damn arrows that hang in the air on raids and don't disappear ! Horrible !  Get 35 melee all flinging arrows on a ranged fight like FR and by 40% your frame rate drops to 1-3 frames per second. This is clearly a bug, becuase a 60 man raid *cannot*  Operate at a collective 1-3 frames per second, period. This needs to be addressed ASAP.  And, it's affecting the entire zones, people at Zone Ins kiting, notice and complain in /ooc about the sudden onset of the tremendous lag.
<br />
I know, not the place for it, but it has caused tremendous difficulty in encounters like Xegony and FR ( typically the longer fights) with the increasing lag due to arrows as the fight progresses.
<br />

<br />
Back on topic, I believe you can fix the pet weapon bug  or pet buffing situation being listed here by quickly recamping. At least it's been working for  my guildies when the bug is noticed.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=266327" target="_blank" class="postlink">Roinin Unsleep</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker - Rodcet Nife</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
